d James Rosenau. Chapters on sex tourism, international markets, and communications technology bring new perspectives to emerging issues. The authors investigate places such as the Dominican Republic, Nigeria, and the Philippines.The contemporary world is defined by globalization. While global human rights standards and institutions have been established, assaults on human dignity continue. These essays identify the new challenges to be faced, and suggest new ways to remedy the costs of globalization.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aGlobalization. 0aHuman rights and globalization. 0aHuman rights. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh1 aBob, Clifford, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrysk, Alison, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrysk, Alison, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCabezas, Amalia Lucia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDonnelly, Jack, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFalk, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFox, Jonathan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMaher, Kristen Hill, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMilner, Wesley T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPangalangan, Raul C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRosenau, James N., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSandholtz, Wayne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWeyker, Shayne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Californi